        <headline>Heat Advisory issued August 21 at 12:34AM PDT until August 23 at 9:00AM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...High temperatures ranging from 99 to 103 degrees and warm
lows between 63 to 72 degrees, with widespread Moderate to Major
HeatRisk.

* WHERE...Northern Washoe County, Western Nevada Basin and Range
including Pyramid Lake, Greater Reno-Carson City-Minden Area, and
Mineral and Southern Lyon Counties.

* WHEN...From noon Friday to 9 AM PDT Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Heat-related illnesses will be more likely, especially
for those spending extended periods outdoors, in poorly cooled
indoor spaces, or who are sensitive to heat.
</description>
        <instruction>Drink plenty of fluids, stay in an air-conditioned room, stay out of
the sun, and check up on relatives and neighbors.</instruction>
